race.comment: ACT NATURAL (1) clearly has ability but she has been very costly for punters who are being asked to take a short price again here. She is placed in all nine career starts but has been defeated as a short-priced favourite several times this campaign. She's versatile and she maps to get the run of the race here for Opperman. She will win one of these and this looks like her chance. BEL RAGAZZO (2) looks a danger. She's been placed in both of her starts and is open to further improvement. She's drawn low and will likely settle in the first four. Pannell sticks. BEL HOTESSE (3) has ability, although her best runs have been in country class maidens. She looks the likely leader and will give some cheek but perhaps she's a better place bet. SASSY LITTLE MISS (9) has shown glimpses of nice ability in jump outs and can run well on debut, while BEYOND MYSTI (7) is another first-starter from a top stable that deserves some thought.
